comment: Material settings of T2 changed from 35 s exposure to 40 s. Global offset is 0.5. Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1). Printed layer looks too thin. It appears that global offset of 0.5  is not enough.

Vol. T1: rest #1 +200 µL (layer 1), +400 L (layer 3). Vol. T2: 400 µL (layer 2). Printed base layer looks okay with thickness. HAMA channels in 1/6 constructs not complete since HAMA ink distribution was off. Otherwise, good result. Constructs collected for analysis.

Vol. T1: 600 µL (layer 1), +400 L (layer 3). Vol. T2: 500 µL (layer 2). Ca. 1.5 mm air bubble in base layer of 1/6 constructs. Otherwise good result, all other constructs complete. Enhanced manual washing after layer 2 (not just dipping, but also rinsing of printed channels with 3x 1 mL fresh DPBS). Constructs collected for analysis.

Vol. T1: rest #3 +200 µL (layer 1), 400 L (layer 3). Vol. T2: 500 µL (layer 2). HAMA channels stable/are not disturbed by washing/dapping. Enhanced manual washing after layer 2 (not just dipping, but also rinsing of printed channels with 3x 1 mL fresh DPBS). Perfect result. Constructs collected for analysis.
